    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Investigating idiosyncrasies in AI fiction",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.03136",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/hjuopb",
      "score": 4,
      "comments": 2,
      "author": "kehn",
      "published": "2026-07-02T12:02:29Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLMs generate highly formulaic fiction, overusing specific vocabulary like 'delve' and 'tapestry' due to RLHF alignment and token probability biases.",
        "Story generation suffers from predictable structural tropes, highlighting the limitations of current temperature, top-k, and top-p sampling methods.",
        "Identifying these narrative idiosyncrasies helps developers build better synthetic text detectors and evaluate LLM creativity and stylistic diversity."
      ]
    },
